  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Preheat</strong> the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7 </p>\r\n<p><strong>Peel</strong>, quarter, and cut the carrots lengthwise into sticks (approx. 6cm long)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Place</strong> on an oven-proof tray and mix well with the honey, cinnamon, and 1-2 tbsp of olive oil</p>\r\n<p><strong>Oven</strong>-roast for 20-25 min, or until caramelized</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Boil</strong> a kettle</p>\r\n<p><strong>Peel</strong> and cut all the potatoes to roughly equal size (approx. 5cm chunks)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the potatoes and salt (optional) to a pot of boiling water and boil for 12 min or until you canbegin to pierce them with a knife (they will continue cooking in step 4)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cut</strong> the leek<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span> in half and wash carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves</p>\r\n<p><strong>Slice</strong> the leek<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span> thinly (approx. 1cm)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the leek to the pot approx. 3 min before the potatoes are completely tender</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> the potatoes and leeks are done drain them, add 15g <span class=\"text-danger\">(30g)</span> of butter and mash</p>\r\n<p><strong>Season</strong> to your taste with salt and pepper and cover until serving</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Check</strong> the carrots and remove from the oven once done</p>\r\n<p><strong>Season</strong> the steaks to your taste on both sides with salt and pepper</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> 1-2 tbsp of olive oil to a pan on a high heat </p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> the oil is hot, add the steaks and cook for 2-4 min on each side or until cooked through to your preference</p>\r\n<p><strong>Remove</strong> the steaks from the pan, cover well and allow to rest for 2 min</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Return</strong> the steak pan to the heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">(150ml)</span> of water, scrape the bottom and stir well </p>\r\n<p><strong>Reduce</strong> by half, remove from the heat and add any juices from the resting meat to make a pan sauce</p>\r\n<p>Tip: For a richer sauce, swirl in a knob of butter just before taking off the heat</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Serve</strong> the mash, carrot and steak together </p>\r\n<p><strong>Drizzle</strong> with the pan sauce</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
  ],
